  <hidden>true</hidden>
  <content>= Description =

The Details macro is a bridge between Confluence and XWiki. It provides a list of related pages based on labels (tags).
= Parameters =

|=Parameter|=Description|=Default
|**id**|The id of the details section.|
|**hidden**|Whether to display the details or not|false

= Examples of usage =

== Visible ==

{{code}}
{{details /}}
{{/code}}

=== Result ===

{{details /}}

== Hidden ==

{{code}}
{{details id="my-page-details" hidden="true" /}}
{{/code}}

=== Result ===

{{details id="my-page-details" hidden="true" /}}

Please inspect the page, because the details are hidden, so you don't see them in the page.</content>
